'''Current Version: 0.7.12'''<br />
BWA is a software package for mapping low-divergent sequences against a large reference genome, such as the human genome. It consists of three algorithms: BWA-backtrack, BWA-SW and BWA-MEM. The first algorithm is designed for Illumina sequence reads up to 100bp, while the rest two for longer sequences ranged from 70bp to 1Mbp. <br /><br />'''Useful Links:'''

* [http://bio-bwa.sourceforge.net/ BWA website]    <br /><br />
